<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8411> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8411" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/7> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "p. 728, footnote 38" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/8042> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #8042" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/5> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Cos. 201. Leg., amb. 196. In MRR 1.337, refer also on this embassy to SIG(3) 591, line 70.\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2572> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2572" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Q. Aelius Paetus succeeded P. Aelius Paetus." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2571> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2571" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 41.21.8-9." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2162> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2162" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "These returned and made their report early in this year (Liv. 35.20.14, and 22.1-2)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2141> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2141" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Sent to Antiochus the Great in Asia when his embassy to Rome failed to secure an agreement (Liv. 34.59.8; 35.13-17)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2086> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2086" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Only Villius is known to have gone to Antiochus in Lysimacheia in 196 (see 196) yet in 193 (Liv. 34.59.8) we find that Sulpicius and Aelius had been there before with him. Holleaux is inclined to reject the explanation that there was a special embassy in 195, when Antiochus did return to Europe (Liv. 34.33.12; see note 3), and to add Sulpicius and Aelius to that of 196; but it is at least possible that they went in 195." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2085> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2085" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Villius reported to Flaminius the return of Antiochus to Europe with larger forces than before (Liv. 34.33.12). Aelius and Sulpicius, also members of the commission of ten legates (see 196) may have been with him (cf. Liv. 34.59.8),\n     and the others occupied elsewhere." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2051> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2051" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Aelius in 193 (Liv. 34.59.8) was one of an embassy that had gone to Antiochus at Lysimacheia before (see 195, note 4). Since his colleagues then were members of this board of ten he should probably be included too." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2050> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2050" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Ten Legati were appointed to assist Flamininus in arranging the peace with Philip and the settlement in Greece (Polyb. 18.42.5; Liv. 33.24.7, cf. 30.1, and 35.1-2). The following are known, and since Livy nowhere lists them in an official order, they are given in alphabetical order." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1981> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1981" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to supplement the colony of Narnia (Liv. 32.2.6-7)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1959> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1959" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Ex quaestura in this passage may indicate that Flamininus was Quaestor in 199 and proceeded immediately to the consulship; cf. ex aedilitate in Liv. 31.4.7, though the more usual expression for \"when aedile\" is qui tum aedilis erat, cf. Liv. 23.24.3; 24.9.4, and 43.6; 29.38.5; 32.7.13, and 27.7. Such phrases, however, can be used when some time elapses between the two offices: cf. Liv. 27.6.17, on Licinius Crassus, who was almost certainly Curule Aedile in 212, and in 210 ex aedilitate gradum ad censuram fecit; and Cic. Phil. 11.11, on Julius Caesar Strabo, who ex aedilitate (90 B.C.) consulatum petit in 88 B.C. Accordingly, Flamininus may have been Quaestor between 203, when he ceased to be in command pro praetore at Tarentum, and 199. He is listed here under the latest possible date." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1958> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1958" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 32.7.1-3; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 121, 452f.; and on Scipio, CIL 1\n     .1, p. 201- Inscr. Ital. 13.3.98. Scipio was chosen Princeps Senatus (Liv. 34.44.4)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1953> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1953" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 31.49.5." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1923> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1923" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Elected through the Pr. Urbanus to assign land in Samnium and Apulia to veterans who had served under Scipio in Africa (Liv. 31.4.1-3, and 49.5). On Villius, see Lübker, no. 1, on Quinctius, no. 4." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1902> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1902" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 30.40.5; Fast. Cap., Degrassi 48f., 121, 452f.; Fast. Fer. Lat., ib. 148f.; Plin. NH 18.166; Chr. 354; Fast. Hyd.; Chr. Pasc.; Oros. 4.19.5, and on Paetus, Dig. 1.2.2.38. Cornelius received command of the fleet and attempted without success to continue the war with Carthage as Scipio's successor (Liv. 30.40.7-15, 43.1, and 44.3; App. Lib. 56 and 62; cf. Dio fr. 59). Aelius in Gaul attacked the Boii and made a treaty with the Ingauni (Liv. 30.40.16, cf. 7-8; 31.2.5-11)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1901> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1901" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/4> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Fast. Cap.: [Cn. Corne]1[ius L. f.] L. n. Lentulus, P. Ail[ius Q. f. P. n. Paitus]. Fast. Fer. Lat.: Cn. Corn[- - - - - -], P. Aelio Q. [- - - - - -]. Lentulus was probably a son of L. Cornelius Lentulus Caudinus, Cos. 237. Paetus\n   \n    1\n   \n   filiation is given in Fast. Cap. for 202." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1878> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1878" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 30.39.4; Fast. Cap.; see above, Dictator." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1839> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1839" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Announced the supplicatio for Scipio's first victory, and the one for Hannibal's departure from Italy (Liv. 30.17.3-6, and 21.10)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1838> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1838" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 29.38.4-5 Provinces 30.1.9, cf. 3.1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1805> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1805" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Liv. 29.38.5 and 8. One of these went with the Legates who investigated charges against Scipio and Pleminius (Liv. 29.20.4 and 11; Diod. 27.4.6; see 205, Legates, on Pleminius; below, Legates, on Caecilius). On Villius, see Lübker no. 1." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1707> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1707" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "P. Aelius Paetus succeeded M. Claudius Marcellus. Liv. 27.36.5, cf. 27.7-11; Plut. Marc. 2.2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/1706> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #1706" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "For Paetus' nomen and cognomen, see Liv. 41.21.8, the notice of his death. See Conway and Johnson on 27.36.5." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/9644> rdfs:label "Post Assertion: #9644" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertion ;
	dprr:isAboutPerson <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/Person/1006> ;
